    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Your Sneak Attack die become d8s and you can reroll any Sneak Attack die of a 1. You must use the new result.</p><p>Also, when you use the Poison option of your Cunning Strike, the target also takes [[/r 2d6]] Poison damage whenever it fails the saving throw. This damage ignores Resistance to Poison damage.</p><section id=\"secret-7vgZrVBoFugesPet\" class=\"secret\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>The <strong>Poison</strong> activity on this feature includes the save and poison damage.</p><p>Alternatively, you can use the inline roll above if you've already used the original activity.</p><p><strong>Important:</strong> This damage does not automatically bypass resistances so ensure the correct damage is being applied.</p></section>",
